Belarussian Player of the Year is a football (soccer) award by Pressbol (Belarussian newspaper Press Ball).
Winners
1983: Sergei Gotsmanov
1985: Sergei Gotsmanov
1987: Sergei Gotsmanov
1989: Sergei Gotsmanov
2001: ?
2002: Aliaksandr Hleb
2003: ?
2004: Aliaksandr Hleb
2005: Aliaksandr Hleb
2006
1st Aliaksandr Hleb ( Arsenal F.C.) 711 points
2nd Sergei Kornilenko ( FC Dnipro Dnipropetrovsk) 422 points
3rd Alexander Kulchy ( FC Tom Tomsk) 200points
